{
  "formula": "module-review",
  "description": "Module Review workflow.\n\nTwo-phase ADR compliance review:\n- Phase 1 (haiku): Fast mechanical scan, creates high-confidence issues\n- Phase 2 (sonnet): Judgment calls, reclassifications, repo-wide issues",
  "version": 1,
  "type": "workflow",
  "vars": {
    "module": {
      "description": "Module path (e.g., 'git', 'databases/meilisearch')",
      "required": true
    },
    "parent": {
      "description": "Parent beads issue ID (e.g., 'dotfiles-pmz.61')",
      "required": true
    },
    "skip_phase2": {
      "description": "Skip Phase 2 even if escalation needed",
      "default": "false"
    }
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "phase1",
      "title": "Phase 1: Mechanical Scan",
      "description": "Fast haiku scan for clear-cut ADR violations.\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Read module files (justfile, data.yml, brewfile, configs)\n2. Read agent spec at `.claude/agents/module-review.md`\n3. Run mechanical checks against ADR-002 through ADR-007\n4. Create beads issues for HIGH confidence findings:\n   ```\n   bd create \"{{module}}: \u003cissue\u003e\" --parent {{parent}} -d \"\u003cdetails\u003e\" -l \"\u003clabels\u003e,\u003cseverity\u003e\" --silent\n   ```\n5. Defer MEDIUM/LOW confidence findings to Phase 2\n6. Update parent task:\n   ```\n   bd update {{parent}} --notes \"Phase 1 complete. N issues created, M deferred\"\n   ```\n\n**Output JSON:**\n```json\n{\n  \"phase\": 1,\n  \"issues_created\": [],\n  \"deferred_findings\": [],\n  \"escalate_to_phase2\": true|false,\n  \"phase2_reasons\": []\n}\n```\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "gate",
      "title": "Phase 2 Gate",
      "description": "Check if Phase 2 is needed.\n\nProceed to Phase 2 if:\n- Phase 1 returned `escalate_to_phase2: true`\n- AND `skip_phase2` variable is not \"true\"\n\nOtherwise, skip Phase 2 and complete workflow.\n",
      "needs": [
        "phase1"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "phase2",
      "title": "Phase 2: Judgment Calls",
      "description": "Sonnet review of ambiguous findings from Phase 1.\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Read module files for deeper context\n2. Read relevant ADRs at `docs/src/adr/`\n3. For each deferred finding:\n   - Confirm as violation → create issue via `bd create`\n   - Reclassify as acceptable → document reason\n   - Identify as repo-wide → create under appropriate epic\n4. Review Phase 1 issues for potential reclassification\n5. Update parent task with final summary:\n   ```\n   bd update {{parent}} --notes \"Review complete. Total: N issues\"\n   ```\n\n**Epic IDs for Repo-Wide Issues:**\n- Justfile Review: dotfiles-4th (lib.just issues)\n- Template Review: dotfiles-02p\n- Secrets Review: dotfiles-c0q\n\n**Output JSON:**\n```json\n{\n  \"phase\": 2,\n  \"issues_created\": [],\n  \"reclassified\": [],\n  \"repo_wide_issues\": [],\n  \"escalate_to_human\": [],\n  \"final_summary\": {}\n}\n```\n",
      "needs": [
        "gate"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "complete",
      "title": "Complete Review",
      "description": "Finalize the module review.\n\n**Actions:**\n1. Verify all issues created correctly\n2. Send completion mail to mayor\n3. Update convoy status if part of batch\n",
      "needs": [
        "phase2"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "source": "/etc/dotfiles/adam/.beads/formulas/module-review.formula.toml"
}
